{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_dewitt_ver01/data/sn86090369/00279520750/1908011701/0064.xml":{"full_text":"EVERY BATH ROOM\nv-i\u00b7-'\n\u00eefivr'\nshould be fitted with a perfect san\nitary system of Piping and Drain\nage. There should be but little\nchance for foul air or stagnant wa\nter to collect In any bowl, tap or\nelbow. Perfect plumbing in a\nhouse often means perfect health\nto the household, and inferior plumb\nlng may mean sickness and\u2014worse.\nLet us have the fixing of your\nhousehold plumbing, and we will\nguarantee to save a lot of your an\nnual doctor bills.\nf. S. CRONK CO.\nMachinist* and Plumbers.\nDealers in Mill, Gin, Plumbing and\nWater Supplies, Metal and Genasco\nRoofing, etc.\nHbe \u00eeDail\u00e7 Xioht\npubllahed Dally Except Sunday\n\u2014BY\nENTERPRISE PUBLISHING\nCOMPANY.\nPAID-UP CAPITAL, *20.000.\nOFFICIOUS and DIRECTORS.\nG. W. McKnlght, President and\nTreasurer; Ed Cunningham, Vice\nPresident; C. W. Kent, Secretary.\nDirectors: T. A. Ferris, G. W. Mc\nKnlght, Ed Cunningham, C. W.Kent,\nDr. C. W. Simpson.\nSUBSCRIPTION RATES\nOne Month I oO\n81i Months (In advance) 2.76\nOne Yejr (In advance) \u03ae 00\nEntered at the \\Vaxahachle Post\noffice as mail matter of the second\nclass.\nObituaries, resolutions ot respect,\ncards of thanks\u2014all matter not\nNEWS\u2014will be charged for at the\nrate of 5 cents per line. Poetry at\ndouble price.\nAny erroneous reflection upon tht\nAaracter, standing or reputation ol\nany person, firm or corporation tnal\nmay appear In the columns of th\u00ab\nDally Light will be gladly corrected\npon lie being brought to the atten\ntlon of the management.\nThe Enterprise Publishing Com\npany Is In uowise responsible foi\ndebt\u00bb that may be contracted by em\nployed, nor will we assume paymenl\nof duch debts under any circum\nstances. Every employe of this offlc\u00ab\nto paid promptly for work done. Thli\nla to protect ourselves and the sell\ning public.\u2014ENTERPRISE PUB\nLISHING COMPANY. Per G. W. Mc\nKnlght, Manager.\nW. A. OWNBY City Editol\n(Residence Phone. Bell No. 289.)\nAN NOU \u039dCEMENTS.\nCongressional\nDistrict Offices\nRepresentative\nCounty Offices\nPrecinct Offices\nCity Aldermen\n$10.OC\n7.5C\n5.0\u00ce\n5.0C\n5.0C\n3.0C\nOther City Offices 5.0C\nTerms strictly in advance.\nAll announcements in this col\numn are maa\u00ab! subject to the actior\nof the democratic primary election!\nIn July.\nFor County Collector\u2014\nTOM FORREST.\nGEO. F. SMITH.\nL. L. JETER.\nFor County Attorney\u2014\nCHARLEY PIPPEN.\nJ. A. LAWSON.\nCITY COMMISSION GOVERNMEN!\nFrank Putnam, whose work 01\nthe Houston Chronicle has givei\nhim some reputation in the rice belt\nhas recently been on a visit to Iowa\nwhich commonwealth he quit, as dii\nJudge Meek, to become a Texan, a\nwou/d thousands of others coul\u00b7\nthey \"let go.\"\nWhile among the Hawkeyes Mr\nPutnam has talked city commissio;\ngovernment, a matter just now un\nder consideration by the Waco citi\nzenship. \"The Iowa plan for cit\ncommission,\" said Mr. Putnam a\nDavenport, \"is in my opinion supei\nior to any of the several plans i\nuse in Texa^ It preserves the essei\ntial feature of deliberative counci\nwhich is virtually eliminated in th\nHouston city charter; and it prt*ser\\\nes to the people through the initia\ntive and referendum and the recal\nthe power to hasten or retard an ad\nministration that might not prov\nable or willing to act as the peopl\nshould deffire. It has another featur\nof great merit\u2014the merit board, \u03bf\ncivil service commission that Is, a\nI understand it, to employ and regu-\nlate the majority of the minor em-!\nployes of the city.\n\"The city commission plan is a\nrecognition of the fact that a city\ngovernment is a business corpora\ntion, and it is nothing else. It brings\ngovernment down out of the clouds\nand sets Its feet firmly on the ground\nThe Texas cities that have tried the\ncity commission plan would no more\ngo Kick to the ward plan than they\nwould go back to the cave era, and\nthe Btone px age of man. They re\ngard both as belonging to the past.\n\"1 would suggest, as Davenport's\nespecial contribution to the city\ncommission plan, that you make\nyour city engineer as nearly inde\npendent of political control as possi\nble; that you pay salary enough for\nthat office to get a first class man,\nand that you make it understood\nthat he is to serve practically for\nlife, or during good behavior.\"\u2014\nWaco Times-Herald.\nMORK DA1RIKS NKKDKI)\nA great part of Texas is very\nmuch asleep on the subject of food,\nwhere it comes from, who pays for\nit, and who gets the money.\nTake, for instance, dairying.\nDallas is paying for 60,000\npounds of butter every week shipped\nin from outside the state, mostly\nfrom Kansas. Fort Worth has some\nprogressive creameries and is taking\ncare of the local situation better,\nsays the Fort Worth Telegram. The\nAlta Vista creamery alone has five\nreceiving stations in Texas for milk\nand cream. The Panther City cream\nery is advertising for all the cream\nit can get. At a maximum all the\nFort Worth Creameries are making\nless than 400 pounds of butter a\nday. They could sell 1,000 pounds\nlocally.\nIn an address before the farmers'\ncongress at Amarillo, C. O. Moser,\ngovernment dairy expert at Denison,\nshowed in simple figures how much\nmoney there Is In dairying by farm\ners, even for those who keep only\nten or twelve dairy cows. A very low\nestimate is $7f> net profit from a\ncow every year.\nIt isn't necessary to ship the milk\nand run the risk of its spoiling in\nshipment. The cream can be shipped\nand two days on the road will not\nspoil it for butter making purposes.\nIn fact cream has to be \"ripened\"\ni before it can be used for butter. The\nskim milk kept at home on the farm\ncan be fed to hogs and poultry.\nFort Worth has a market for sev\neral thousand pounds of cream a\nday. The packing houses are scour\ning the country all the time for more\nmilk and cream to use in connection\nwith their butterine products, but\nj the local creameries are the princi\nI pal market.\nThe farmer 200 miles from Fort\nWorth has almost the same advan\nI tage as the one ten miles away. The\nexpress on shipments is a little more\nj but on the other hand the land de\ni voted to dairying is cheaper. He is\nat less expense.\nA popular illustration used by a\nTexas insurance company pictures a\ncow which is feeding in Texas and\nbeing milked iu New York. The il\nlustration applies to Texas money\ngoing out of the state for life insur\nance premiums.\nThe illustration can be applied as\naptly to dairying. Dallas is paying\nout at the rate of over $700,000 a\nyear for butter produced outside the\nI state. A local creamery man said\nthis week:\n\"If it were not for Kansas and\n\u03b9 Missouri Texas would starve for\nj butter, or else eat oleomargerine.\"\nI Why should Kansas farmers get the\nI money that is waiting for the farm\nj ers of Texas?\nThe state needs more dairies and\ni needs them right away.\nThere's nothing like something to\nj sell when you go to town, and di\nversification will help you along\u2014\nwill fill your wagon every time you\nstart to town, and you can haul it\nback in cash or something you need.\n\u2014Greenville Banner.\nI A physician insists that what is\ncalled grip is nothing but influenza,\nj This settles nothing except that, in\nfluenza is much more fiendish than\nhas been supposed.\n\u038a\nSnap Shots in the Dallas News\nvery truthfully observes: \"You may\nbe a Napoleon of finance, but if you\ndo not pay your poll tax you can\nt j\nnot vote.\nMurder often results from a sim\nI pie booze storm, to speak in unpol\nished vernacular. Have the experts\nand alienists every analyzed this?\nYou can't ride on the band wagon\nthis year unless you provide your\nself with a poll tax receipt.\n\u03b9 The man who does not pay hie\n\u00ee poll tax has no right to complain If\nr an unwholesome law Is enacted by\n\u03b9 the legislature.\nWINTKH BASKETBALL 1\\ TKXAS!\n\u03b9\n\nSeason I uau^ui atrd at San Antonio\nProving a Success.\nSail Antonio, Texas, Jan. 17.-\u2014j\nWinter baseball inaugurated here\non New Year's day has been found\nto be quite a success, owing to the \u03b9\nmild, sunny weather and is destined I\nto become one of the features of the\ntourist season of San Antonio. So 1\nfar only a local team made up partly\nof Texas league ball players who are\nwintering here and a sprinkling of\namateurs have played. News, how\never, is received from Chicago of\nthe coming of the White Sox a little\nlater to go into training here. As\nSan Antonio has some ten thousand\nwinter tourists here continuously\nevery winter as well as a large pleas\nure loving population, there is a\nfine chance to make the winter base\nball a paying feature as well as a\ngood training for the northern base\nball season.\nRECORl\u00bb OP FAILURES.\nWestern District of Texas Shows\nDecrease as Compared to 1 (MKt.\nSan Antonio, Texas. Jan. 17.\u2014\nFewer failures in 1907 than in the\nprosperous year of 1906 is the rec\nord made by fourteen counties com\nj prising the western district of Tex\nas in R. G. Dunn's report. There\nwere seventeen failures in this part\nof Texas in 1907 against 21 in 1906.\nI Furthermore the assets in the fail\nures of 1907 showed an excess over\nthe Habilites of $176,940, whereas\nin 1906 the assets were only $6,650 j\nover the liabilities. This fine show\ning made in spite of a great finan\ncial disturbance and on the heels of\nthe hottest and dryest summer in 2 2\nyears, is a gratifying proof of the\nj prosperity of Southwest Texas. Cop\nious rains during the past two\nI months and rapid recovery of eon\ni fidence makes the business outlook\nj for 1908 most promising.\nFINI\u00bb HERRING XOT GUILTY.\nj Jury Considers Case Most of Thurs\nday and Renders Verdict Late\nin (lie Afternoon.\nFort Worth. Texas, Jan. 17.\u2014The\njury in the D. B. Herring murder\ncase, after being out since early\nWednesday returned a verdict of not\nguilty late yesterday afternoon.\nHerring was tried in the sixty\nseventh district court on the charge\nof killing Dr. De Shazzar at Arling\nton last August. De Shazzar's skull\nwas split with an ax.\nEvelyn Thaw Nerve Remedy.\nNew York. Jan. 17.\u2014Nervous?\nIrritable? Out of sorts? All run\ndo^vn? Try the Evelyn Thaw nerve\nremedy, which has enabled that\nyoung woman to pass through or\nI\u00abali A-hich would have killed other\nwomen. H^re it Is:\nRetire early. Avoid all beverages\nor foods which are calculated to pro\nduce insomnia. Sleep eight or nine\nhours. Exercise in the open air.\nSleep with window open. Take a\ncold bath every morning. To quiet\nnerves, place a sponge saturated\nwith cold water at the base of the\nbrain, allowing the water to trickle\ndown the spine. Drink two quarts of\nrich milk every day. Last, don't wor\nry.\nI Chilli Smothers Near Denton.\nDenton, Texas, Jan. 17.\u2014When\nJ. A. Pearson and his wife arose\nyesterday morning they found that\ntheir child, ten days old, had during\nthe night slipped down under the\nheavy bed covering and smothered.\nPearson is a farmer, living east of\nthis place.\nk\u00bbh<i ib<* Advertisement\u00b7'\nll\u2014WII >.\u00b7-\u038a-\u03b7\u039c\u039c\u039c\u039a\u039c\u039c\u039c\u039c\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7*\nKon't I tin \u03b9\u03b9\u03b9>\u00b7 Your Physician\nif medicine prescribed by him\ndoes not have the desired effect\u2014\nperhaps you did not get what you\nordered. We guarantee the careful\nand exact filling of all doctors' pre\nscriptions, the use of pure drugs\nwhich have not lost their strength,\nand their compounding according to\nthe be\u00a3t. most reliable methods.\n\u03c4\nCALVIN BROS.,\nCorrect Men's Furnishers Waxahachie, Texas\nIF IT'S NEW, IT'S HERE\nW/\u0388 have just received a large\ns1 assortment of Poultry Wire\nand are prepared to serve you with\nany,size desired\ni WAXAHACHIE HARDWARE\n5 COMPANY\n\n\n\nThe Next Or